        <div class="faq-wrapper">
            <h2 style="text-align: center; font-size: 36px; margin-bottom: 40px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>How much can I earn as a Super Host?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Super Hosts earn competitive rates based on their qualifications and the subjects they teach. Rates typically range from $45-$75 per hour, with additional performance bonuses and referral incentives. Your earnings depend on your availability and the number of students you take on.
                </div>
            </details>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Do I need my own teaching materials?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    No. The Study Zone provides all teaching materials, worksheets, and resources. You'll have access to our comprehensive curriculum library and digital tools. You're welcome to supplement with your own materials if you prefer.
                </div>
            </details>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>What if I need to cancel a session?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    We require 24 hours notice for cancellations. We understand emergencies happen and handle them on a case-by-case basis. We'll work with you to reschedule the session with the student.
                </div>
            </details>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Can I choose which students I work with?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Yes. We match you with students based on your expertise, availability, and preferences. If a student isn't a good fit, we'll find a better match. Your comfort and success are our priorities.
                </div>
            </details>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Is there a minimum commitment?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    We ask for a minimum commitment of 10 hours per week to ensure consistency for our students. However, you have full flexibility in setting your schedule. You can increase or decrease your hours with 2 weeks notice.
                </div>
            </details>
            
            <details class="faq-item">
